Description:

Added JMAP conditional-set support via the new
`urn:ietf:params:jmap:conditional` capability
(draft-gondwana-jmap-conditional).  Foo/set methods now accept an
optional `ifUnchangedBy` argument: a map of object id to a PatchObject
representing the state the caller last saw.  Before applying any
requested change, the server checks whether applying that patch to the
current server-side object would be a no-op.  If the object has changed
since the client last fetched it the per-object SetError
`stateMismatch` is returned; if the patch itself is structurally
invalid, `invalidPatch` is returned.  The check is per-object and
composes with the existing `ifInState` whole-method guard.

Datatypes covered: ContactCard, Email, CalendarEvent, Mailbox, Note,
SieveScript, VacationResponse, EmailSubmission, AddressBook, Calendar,
CalendarNotification, and Principal.


Documentation:

https://www.ietf.org/archive/id/draft-gondwana-jmap-conditional.txt


Config changes:

None


Upgrade instructions:

Nothing required; the capability is advertised automatically.
Clients that do not send `ifUnchangedBy` are unaffected.


